messages.message: I'm writing up the docs for text editor today. Sorry for delay!

hi all, because docs are _in_ the product, we have a Jira for each doc deliverable. @John St looks like you have a doc Jira for the text editor https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/UX-198 Hint: watch this nifty 4 mins. How to work with IB docs (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8IiD5ajbXck&amp=&feature=youtu.be) video, and then
let me know how I can help you get started with the Markdown file and PR.
Kudos John on the awesome release notes for the text editor!

@Felicia's https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/INSIGHTS-1000 is an excellent example of: Jira with Affects versions and Fix versions, self-describing PR branch name, and belongs to an Epic Jira.
